description:
About the team 

 FX Services is part of Currencies & Emerging Markets and provides spot and forward FX pricing and processing capabilities to internal JPMorgan business lines, namely: Securities Services, Wholesale Payments, Commercial Bank and Consumer & Business Banking. In collaboration with Securities Services, FX Services manages a Passive Currency Overlay programme which is offered to Asset Managers looking to mitigate currency risk associated with both their global investments, as well as the domicile of their investors. 


The role 

 The individual will be part of the Front Office Product team within FX Services, responsible for designing and implementing data science tools and methods to drive market leading client solutions and formulation of business strategy. The Product team works closely with Sales, Trading, Operations and Technology, and partners across Markets and Securities Services to develop and deliver these solutions. This is an exciting role for a creative individual with a strong analytical background and a desire to apply their skills in a stimulating and fast paced environment. 

 Based in London, the role will report directly to the Global Passive Currency Overlay Product Head. 


Core Responsibilities: 


Analyze multiple large data sets and apply advanced statistical, data science and machine learning methods; 
Develop interactive dashboards to present insights using data visualization tools and techniques; 
Build predictive models and scalable data products; 
Drive technology implementation and integration of the new data products. 


Experience / Competencies: 


Strong academic background in a STEM discipline such as Financial Engineering, Applied Mathematics, Physics, Engineering and Computer Science; 
Extensive experience with Python, R, SQL and software engineering fundamentals; 
Experience with advanced statistical modeling and machine learning techniques; 
Experience with data visualization tools like Tableau; 
Proven ability to analyze large data sets and translating insights into actionable business recommendations; 
Highly motivated and able to collaborate effectively combined with a practical approach to problem solving and an ability to explain complex topics to a diverse range of audiences; 
Great team skills. Must be a self-starter and have ability to work under pressure; 
Passion to learn and keep abreast of new technologies and data methods. 

J.P. Morgan is a global leader in financial services, providing strategic advice and products to the world's most prominent corporations, governments, wealthy individuals and institutional investors. Our first-class business in a first-class way approach to serving clients drives everything we do. We strive to build trusted, long-term partnerships to help our clients achieve their business objectives.
 We recognize that our people are our strength and the diverse talents they bring to our global workforce are directly linked to our success. We are an equal opportunity employer and place a high value on diversity and inclusion at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of any protected attribute, including race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital or veteran status, pregnancy or disability, or any other basis protected under applicable law. In accordance with applicable law, we make reasonable accommodations for applicants' and employees' religious practices and beliefs, as well as any mental health or physical disability needs.
